<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Alablaster" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Alablaster,</orth> (M. Edd. <emph>alabaster</emph>), a kind of gypsum: <cit><quote>ivory in an a. band,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 363" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 363</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>her a. skin,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 419" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 419</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>cut in a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 1.1.84" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 1, 84</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a. arms,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.3.11" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 3, 11</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>smooth as monumental a.</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 5.2.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. V, 2, 5</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>